results.name: Number of z-blobs summing to n. Number of connected strict integer partitions of n, with pairwise indivisible parts, that cannot be capped by a z-tree.
comment: Caps of a clutter are defined in the link, and the generalization to "multiclutters," where edges can be multisets, is straightforward.
link: Gus Wiseman, Every Clutter Is a Tree of Blobs, The Mathematica Journal, Vol. 19, 2017.
